&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Media Workflow Engineer at Peloton, you will serve as the technical foundation for our post-production and broadcast ecosystems. This role is a 50/50 blend of high-impact project delivery and mission-critical operational support. You will act as the lead architect for our Media Asset Management (MAM) and workflow platforms, ensuring our content engine runs at peak performance in a dynamic, global broadcast environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR DAILY IMPACT AT PELOTON&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the maintenance of our MAM (Backlight Iconik) and shared storage infrastructures (OpenDrives, Quantum)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and optimize automated workflows on premises and on cloud based workflows. Transcoding pipelines using Telestream Vantage, Hiscale FLICS, and GLIM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary technical lead for metadata taxonomy, video codecs, and delivery specifications, ensuring seamless integration across software and cloud engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expert-level support for Mac, Linux, and Windows server environments while maintaining high-fidelity technical documentation for our evolving architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Post-Production and Broadcast teams to translate creative needs into robust technical solutions, from cloud-based archiving to infrastructure upgrades&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a crucial member of our agile team, you will assist with Proof of Concept (PoC) testing of new technologies. You will investigate emerging tools to support RFPs, ensuring you have a strong voice and meaningful influence on the direction of our systems and workflow tech stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical liaison for third-party vendors to maintain, troubleshoot, and optimize mission-critical software and hardware, ensuring our systems remain resilient and up to date&lt;/li&gt;
