&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Trade Compliance Analyst, you will play an integral part in executing Peloton’s Customs policies and procedures, with a primary focus on compliance with US Customs and Border Protection (CBP) and Canada Border Services Agency (CBSA) regulations. Reporting to Peloton’s Senior Manager, Trade Compliance, you will oversee Peloton’s Customs brokers, ensure timely, accurate &amp;amp; compliant payments of import tariffs, and generally maintain &amp;amp; strengthen Peloton’s “reasonable care” controls.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for this role challenges themself to continuously improve Peloton’s global trade compliance program, partnering cross-functionally with a variety of stakeholders (external service providers, Product, Legal, Finance, Supply Chain, Operations and Logistics).&lt;/p&gt;
